                                <text_1091121937
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2022-12-07T05:33:30.724-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="kumarvx60"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2022-12-08T04:45:40.696-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="kumarvx60"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>Mohita Kumar, M.D., understands the everyday burdens caused by uterine fibroids: She deals with the condition herself.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                                <separator_copy_copy_432814022
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756409908]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2022-12-07T04:23:38.517-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="kumarvx60"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2022-12-07T04:23:38.517-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="kumarvx60"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <title_copy_2073259397
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545825678,1651545825694]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2022-11-30T02:11:17.530-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="kumarvx60"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-04-18T10:49:47.051-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="A silent agony"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h2"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2022-12-01T03:08:11.212-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="kumarvx60"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2022-12-08T04:47:28.442-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="kumarvx60"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>All the symptoms were there: menstrual pain and heavy bleeding. Fatigue. Anemia. But Mohita Kumar had become accustomed to a rocky “time of the month”…every month.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“You think that’s just the way you are,” she says.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>One day, Kumar’s boss took one look at her ghostly-white complexion and told her, “You need to go home. You don’t look right.”&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Kumar followed her boss’s advice. When she arrived home, she collapsed onto the floor and passed out. A few hours later, she woke up, light-headed, and knew the time had come to talk with her OB/GYN about her bleeding and other symptoms.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Her doctor ordered an ultrasound and that’s when the diagnosis came: uterine fibroids – non-cancerous masses of uterine tissue that made her&amp;nbsp;normal menstruation a nightmare.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>What surprised Kumar the most was that she had missed it: Kumar, herself, is a physician.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“I think doctors can be some of the most non-compliant patients in the world,” says Kumar, a physician and AbbVie researcher. Also, she admits she loves her work and doesn’t like taking time away for extra doctor’s visits.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>But she believes there’s another reason she underestimated the problem.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“You’re told by your mom and your aunts, ‘Oh, this is normal,’” she explains. “You come to believe this is just what having a period is like. So you don’t make a big deal about it. And women don’t talk about their periods, in general.”&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                            </container4>
